The paper discusses algorithms for learning deep generative models, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The focus is on Helmholz machines, which are a specific type of generative model. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also includes experiments on image datasets, which suggests that it may be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
